===Verb===
[[Category:English irregular verbs]]
{{en-verb|throws|throwing|threw|thrown}}

# To make an [[object]] [[fly]] through the [[air]].
# To [[eject]] or cause to fall off.
#: '''''throw''' a shoe; throw a rod''
# To move to another [[position]]; [[displace]].
#: '''''throw''' the switch''
# (''ceramics'') To make a [[pot]] by pulling [[clay]] as it turns on a [[wheel]].
#: ''to '''throw''' a pot''
# {{Cricket}} Of a [[bowler]], to [[deliver]] the ball [[illegal]]ly by [[straighten]]ing the [[bowling]] arm during delivery.
# {{computing}} To interrupt normal processing by sending an error to an [[exception-handling]] mechanism.
#:''If the file is readonly, the method '''throws''' an invalid operation exception.''
#:<code>''if(this.IsReadonly)''</code>
#::<code>'''''throw''' new System.InvalidOperationException("Cannot write to readonly file.");''</code>

